00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,430
Amazon OpenSearch Overview.

2
00:00:03,300 --> 00:00:07,630
Amazon OpenSearch Service is a managed service that makes it easy to deploy,

3
00:00:07,780 --> 00:00:11,440
operate, and scale open-search clusters in the AWS Cloud.

4
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:13,750
Amazon OpenSearch Service is

5
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:16,490
the successor to Amazon Elasticsearch Service and

6
00:00:16,490 --> 00:00:19,180
supports OpenSearch and legacy Elasticsearch.

7
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,040
OpenSearch is a fully open-source search and

8
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:25,260
analytics engine for use cases such as log analytics,

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,180
real-time application monitoring,

10
00:00:27,310 --> 00:00:28,790
and clickstream analysis.

11
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:31,520
Amazon OpenSearch Service provisions

12
00:00:31,530 --> 00:00:33,860
all the resources for your cluster and launches it.

13
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:37,550
It also automatically detects and replaces failed nodes,

14
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:41,320
reducing the overhead associated with self-managed infrastructures.

15
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:45,840
You can scale your cluster with a single API call or a few clicks in the console.

16
